        <h1>LeetCode 190: Reverse Bits (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Reverse the bits of a given 32-bit unsigned integer. For example, the 32-bit integer represented in
                binary as 00000010100101000001111010011100 should be reversed to 00111001011110000010100101000000.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: n = 00000010100101000001111010011100<br>
                Output: 964176192 (00111001011110000010100101000000)<br>
                Explanation: The input binary is reversed bit by bit to produce the output.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int reverseBits(int num) {
        unsigned int reversed = 0;
        
        for (int bitIndex = 0; bitIndex &lt; 32; bitIndex++) {
            reversed &lt;&lt;= 1;                // Make space for next bit
            reversed |= (num &amp; 1);         // Append extracted bit to result
            num &gt;&gt;= 1;                     // Shift input to process next bit
        }
        
        return reversed;
    }
};</code></pre>
